SCP-015 Incident D

After the transfer of SCP-015's mass to the site, a number of unexplained changes have begun to develop. Notably, SCP-015 now grows at a radically faster rate than previously recorded, requiring several sessions of scheduled maintenace a day. This has placed an unforeseen burden on the site's staff, and we are looking for an automated solution to the problem.

Addendum A: After an additional week of observation post-transfer, several cracks in the walls of the chamber have been identified, which will require an elevated amount of care to maintain. It is now proposed that SCP-015 be removed and returned to the site back to its original site, but it is still unclear if these behavioral changes are permanent or environmental in nature, further testing is necessary.